The paper proposes a new approach for representing graphs as an infinite time-series, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing methods for representing graphs as real-valued vectors, which is a topic related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on combinatorial optimization problems, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE).
